entry.title: Return field type used for filling
entry.content:
Currently, Autofill uses only the field type to fill that field. In the

future, a system will be implemented to allow some field types to

fallback to another type in case it does not have a value to fill. This

CL builds part of the infrastructure for such a change.



More precisely, this CL:

- Renames GetValueFor(Profile|CreditCard) to

GetFillingValueAndTypeFor(Profile|CreditCard)

- Makes the two functions above return also the type used to retrieve

the filling value.

entry.title: [iOS] Use DiffableDataSource for PageInfo table view
entry.content:
This CL updates the PageInfo, to use the DiffableDataSource API

instead of the custom Chrome API.

This change include:

- Using translation between the enum and NSNumber

- Register/dequeue the cells manually

- Handle the header/footer manually

- Handle the cells manually



The main functional change is that the data are now "pulled" when

displayed instead of being stored in the item (i.e. when the Table

View wants to display the cell we look at the value from the

permissionsInfo instead of looking at the permissionsInfo at the

creation time).



This CL is also adding helpers to register/dequeue cell and headers

more easily.

It is also creating a new base class to be able to handle the

empty view and other things if needed in the future.



But on the other end, those changes mean that:

- Reloading the cell is much easier: as the information are looked up

when the TableView is asking for it, the only action is to ask for

the item to be reloaded.

- The Switch delegate is handled at the same time as the switch cell

configuration

entry.title: Introduce the keyboard focus bit for autofill sub-popups.
entry.content:
This CL makes it possible to handle keyboard events in

a parent popup with a sub-popup open. Walking through

the parent suggestions by keyboard is one of the requirements for

the non-selectable suggestions functionality, but this CL also

changes the regular suggestions behavior, as implicitly changing

the recipient with providing no visual clues (like selecting

a suggestion) may be frustrating to the user.



This CL also adds a check for `nullptr` from `WebContents::GetTopLevelNativeWindow()` in `BoundsOverlapWithAnyOpenPrompt()`. It returns `nullptr` in unit test runs on Mac and causes CHECK crash in subsequent `GetViewForWindow()` call. The crash is revealed in this CL because updated `PopupViewViewsTest` (`set_element_bounds()`) changed the logic of early `false` return in `PopupViewViews::DoUpdateBoundsAndRedrawPopup()`.

entry.title: Separate methods for fetching manifests and segments for EXT-X-MAP
entry.content:
The EXT-X-MAP tag allows a manifest to declare the URI/range of a

leading chunk of data which should be prefixed to every sequence of

media segments declared later in the file. As a result of this,

each media segment may need to fetch multiple URI/range pairs in

order to parse properly. This is especially common for fragmented

mp4 content, where the mp4 headers are stored at a single URI, and

content is fragmented across other URIs.



This CL separates HlsRenditionHost::ReadFromUrl into two methods:

HlsRenditionHost::StreamManifest

HlsRenditionHost::StreamMediaSegment



which allows constructing the proper queue of segments for a media

segment fetch, while keeping a simple interface for streaming a

manifest.

entry.title: Reapply "IDB: add/improve some performance metrics."
entry.content:
This reverts commit ce1ab8f3aac6d2f02bbb1ddb1df189ab18d2d2f7.



Change to original: make browser test wait for transaction commit

before calling `done()`. Without this step, the browser side

verifications are racy.



Original change's description:

> IDB: add/improve some performance metrics.

>

> The long-existing Transaction.*.TimeActive metric starts measuring from

> when a transaction "starts" and stops measuring when it's half way

> through committing, i.e. when done writing blobs (if any), but not done

> with the LevelDB commit. Not clear if this was intentional, but it's

> being replaced by `TimeActive2` which measures until after the LevelDB

> commit finishes, which should better capture differences between

> backing stores (e.g. LevelDB vs SQLite) as well as the effects of

> relaxed durability.

>

> A new renderer metric is added that measures the time taken to open a

> database, which can either be establishing a new connection to an

> existing database or creating a new database. This is an important

> aspect of read performance which the `ObjectStoreGet` metric fails to

> measure since it doesn't start measuring until the transaction is

> already active. `open` delays could be affected by IDB thread

> contention (crbug.com/1474996) or database lock contention, i.e.

> those resources guarded by PartitionedLockManager; relaxing

> durability should generally shorten the duration for which locks are

> held, so hopefully this metric demonstrates a difference in that

> experiment.

>

> A new browser metric, Transaction.*.TimeQueued, measures the time

> spent in the transaction queue before starting. Like the new renderer

> metric, this should capture "traffic jams" from lock or thread

> contention.

>

entry.content:

was causing some reads to come back as smaller than the requested size.

fully buffered. This means that reading a full stream will now take one

extra call to `ReadExistingDataSource` to get a zero size read back. The

tests are updated to reflect this.

entry.title: Implement Multi-URL data source streams for EXT-X-MAP implementation
entry.content:
The EXT-X-MAP tag allows a manifest to declare the URI/range of a

leading chunk of data which should be prefixed to every media segment

declared later in the file. As a result of this, each media segment may

need to fetch multiple URI/range pairs in order to parse properly. This

is especially common for fragmented mp4 content, where the mp4 headers

are stored at a single URI, and content is fragmented across other URIs.



This first CL modifies HLSDataSourceProvider to accept a queue of

URI/Range segments instead of a single URI and range. There are no

changes to the current use of HlsDataSourceProvider, which will come in

subsequent CLs.



R=dalecurtis
